					<note>
						<hi rend="bold">Colophon details:</hi> 
							<hi rend="bold">Date:</hi>  Undated 
							<hi rend="bold">Scribe:</hi> <persName xml:lang="en" role="scr">Anonymous</persName>.
					</note>
					<note><hi rend="bold">Colophon further notes:</hi> There is no colophon - the work is possibly incomplete at the end.</note>
					<note>
						<hi rend="bold">Note concerning work: </hi>A manual of Shīʿite theology and metaphysics. The author, Mīr Dāmād, is very likely one and the same as the author of King's 8, <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_315085888">Mīr Muḥammad Bāqir Dāmād</persName>, in which case his date of death is earlier, 1040/1631. See S.H. Rizvi, "Mīr Dāmād in India: Islamic Philosophical Traditions and the Problem of Creation", <title>Journal of the American Oriental Society</title>, vol. 131 (2011), pp. 9-23.
					</note>
